cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper deals with security issues in cloud computing, specifically the problem of side-channel attacks between collocated virtual machines. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves optimization of performance and power consumption, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of game theory suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another likely category. The paper also involves decision-making and control, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves modeling and analysis, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
